    "last_activity_date" : 1523924261,
    "last_edit_date" : 1523924261,
    "creation_date" : 1351448275,
    "answer_id" : 13111620,
    "question_id" : 642897,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can not change the length of an array, but you can change the values the index holds by copying new values and store them to a existing index number.\n1=mike , 2=jeff // 10 = george 11 goes to 1 overwriting mike .</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object[] array = new Object[10];\nint count = -1;\n\npublic void myFunction(String string) {\n    count++;\n    if(count == array.length) { \n        count = 0;  // overwrite first\n    }\n    array[count] = string;    \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
